    <name>
				<text>38.2.1.2 Find the mean, standard deviation and cumulative distribution function</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p><p>A<span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">&nbsp;protective coating applied to a conductor designed to work in corrosive conditions. The thickness of this coating, \(X\), follows a uniform distribution over the interval \([{@low_bound@}\mu\text{m},{@upp_bound@}\mu\text{m}]\).&nbsp; Find the expectation, standard deviation and the probability that the thickness of the coating is less than or equal to \( {@case@}\mu\text{m}\) thick.</span></p><p>\( \text{E}(X) = \) [[input:ans1]] \(\mu\text{m}\)[[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</p><p>\( \sigma(X) = \) [[input:ans2]] \(\mu\text{m}\) [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]</p><p>\( \text{P}(X\leq {@case@})=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt3]]<br></p><p><strong>Syntax hint</strong>: To enter \(\sqrt{2}\) use \(\texttt{sqrt(2)}\)</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Let the random variable \(X\) denote the thickness of the coating, then \(X \sim \text{Uniform}({@low_bound@}, {@upp_bound@})\) with probability density function:</p><p>\[f(x) = \left\{\begin{array}{ll}&nbsp;0, &amp; \text{if $x &lt; {@low_bound@}$},\\ \dfrac{1}{{@upp_bound-low_bound@}}, &amp; \text{if ${@low_bound@} \leq x\leq {@upp_bound@}$},\\&nbsp;0, &amp; \text{if $x &gt; {@upp_bound@}$}.\end{array}\right.\]</p><p><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">Using the formulae developed for the mean and variance gives:</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">\[\begin{align*} \text{E}(X) &amp;= \dfrac{{@low_bound@} + {@upp_bound@}}{2} = {@ta1@},\\ \text{V}(X) &amp;= \dfrac{({@upp_bound@} - {@low_bound@})^2}{12} = {@VX@}.\end{align*}\]</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">This means that the expected value for the thickness of the coating is \(\text{E}(X) = {@ta1@}\mu\text{m}\) and the standard deviation in the coating thickness is \(\sigma(X) = \sqrt{{@VX@}} = {@ta2@}\mu\text{m}\).</span></p><p>The cumulative distribution function for this uniform random variable is:</p><p></p><p>\[F(x) = \left\{\begin{array}{ll}&nbsp;0, &amp; \text{if $x &lt; {@low_bound@}$},\\ \dfrac{x-{@low_bound@}}{{@upp_bound-low_bound@}}, &amp; \text{if ${@low_bound@} \leq x\leq {@upp_bound@}$},\\ 1, &amp; \text{if $x &gt; {@upp_bound@}$}.\end{array}\right.\]</p>Therefore, the probability that the thickness of the coating is less than or equal to \({@case@}\mu\text{m}\) is:<br>\[\text{P}(X\leq {@case@}) = F({@case@}) =&nbsp;\dfrac{{@case@}-{@low_bound@}}{{@upp_bound-low_bound@}} = {@ta3@}.\]<br>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
